HEADWORD: Eye-minded
<hw>Eye"-mind`ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having one's mental imagery
prevailingly of the visual type; having one's thoughts and memories
mainly in the form of visual images.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Eye"-mind`ed*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

